<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#88)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-88">
                                <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi></head>
                                <p>—No minutes of this conversation have been found. The
                                    conversation and the subject discussed are referred to, however,
                                    in the following memorandum of July 24 (in the <persName corresp="#p_TJV1">Truman</persName> Papers) by <persName corresp="#p_VCJKJ1">Captain James K. Vardaman,
                                        Jr.</persName>, Naval Aide to the President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Remind the President Wednesday morning to write a letter
                                            to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CJCM1">Churchill</persName>
                                            and send him a copy of telegram despatched to
                                            Generalissimo <persName corresp="#p_CK1">Chiang Kai
                                                Shek</persName> and also copy of revised Lend Lease
                                            document read to <persName corresp="#p_CJCM1">Churchill</persName> by <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> on the porch
                                            this morning.”<note n="1" xml:id="d710a-88fn1">For the
                                                letter which was sent to <persName corresp="#p_CJCM1">Churchill</persName> on July
                                                25, see <ref target="#d1183">documents Nos.
                                                  1183</ref> and <ref target="#d1248">1248</ref>,
                                                  <hi rend="italic">post</hi>. The “revised Lend
                                                Lease document” referred to has not been identified.
                                                Cf. the enclosure to <ref target="#d1185">document
                                                  No. 1185</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note></p>
                                    </quote></p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>